	<div class="Box">
		<div class="boxTitle">What are cookies?</div>
	    <div class="boxContent">
			<p>A cookie is a small text that your browser receives from the web page you just visited and that serves to remember the information of the visit, such as the selected language and other settings. In this way, the next visit will automatically adjust to the preferences of the visitor, and the web will be more practical and useful to the user.</p>
	    </div>
    </div>
    <div class="Box">
	    <div class="boxTitle">Why do we use cookies?</div>
	    <div class="boxContent">
			<p>For many reasons, such as to facilitate the registration in our service and to protect the data. They are also used so that the advertising that appears in our web is adjusted as much as possible to the interests of each user.</p><br>
			<h4>What kind of cookies do you use {@name}?</h4>
			<p>Below you can see the list with the most used cookies in {@name}. Our Privacy Policy explains in detail how we protect the data of our users in the use of cookies, as well as all information related to data protection.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Safety</span>: We use security cookies to authenticate users, prevent fraudulent use of login credentials, and protect user data against unauthorized actions. This category includes authentication cookies, as in the Uses category.</li>
				<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Applications</span>: Cookies in this category serve to make the website work and offer services according to the expectations of visitors, such as browsing the web pages or access to secure areas. Without these cookies the web could not function correctly, here the preferences, loading processes and session states are included.</li>
				<li><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Advertising</span>: These cookies make the advertising more in line with the interests of the users and more valuable to the advertisers. For example, through cookies we can know the interests of users and offer products and services that fit their needs. We can also use a cookie to see if the person who is watching a particular ad on {@name} then visits the advertiser's website. In the same way our partners use cookies, or other similar technology, to determine if we are showing an advertisement and how it provides us with necessary information about the user's interaction with him. You also work with the advertiser by showing your ad inside or outside {@name}, after the user has visited your web or application, this may require the use of cookies, local storage on the device or other similar technologies. & Nbsp; For the insertion of advertising on the web and inside the Hotel we work with Adtech and Google Adsense (both developed by Google). </ Li> <li> </ li> <li> For content and tracking cookies </ span>: Our site may include one or more social plug-in modules. These modules allow social networking users to share content with their friends (as well as propose other related features such as editorial comments). These plug-ins and Access Cookies allow social networks to identify members who make use of them. Our social plugins are Twitter, Facebook, Janrain and Comufy.</li>
			</ul>
	    </div>
